                type="document" xml:id="d738">
                <head>No. 738<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>From January 31 to February 1, 1953, Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">John Foster Dulles</persName> and Director for Mutual
                    Security <persName corresp="#p_STASSENHE1">Harold E. Stassen</persName> visited
                    Rome as part of a 9-day tour of Western Europe. On January 31 <persName
                        corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_STASSENHE1">Stassen</persName> met privately with Prime Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_DEGASPERIA1">Alcide De Gasperi</persName>; the three
                    men later were joined by Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_BUNKERE1">Ellsworth
                        Bunker</persName> and other United States Embassy officials and by Italian
                    Minister of the Budget <persName corresp="#p_PELLAG1">Giuseppe Pella</persName>,
                    Minister of Defense <persName>Randolfo Pacciardi</persName>, and other Italian
                    officials. These conversations <pb facs="0514" n="1604" xml:id="pg_1604"/> were
                    described in telegram 4275 from Paris, February 1, and in <persName
                        corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName>’ message to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName>, also dated February 1. For
                    texts, see <ref target="frus1952-54v05p2#pg_1551">volume V, Part 2, pages
                        1551</ref> and <ref target="frus1952-54v05p2#pg_1553">1553</ref>.</p>
            </div>
